.TH "radeon_sa_event" 9 "radeon_sa_event" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
radeon_sa_event \- Check if we can stop waiting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" radeon_sa_event
.BI "(struct radeon_sa_manager *sa_manager "  ","
.BI "unsigned size "  ","
.BI "unsigned align "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sa_manager" 12
pointer to the sa_manager
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes we want to allocate
.IP "align" 12
alignment we need to match
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check if either there is a fence we can wait for or
enough free memory to satisfy the allocation directly
